+Run a job a limited number of times
+~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
+
+Use ``max_runs(n)`` to remove a job after it has executed ``n`` times.
+It can appear anywhere in the job's fluent configuration.
+
+.. code-block:: python
+
+    import schedule
+
+    def job():
+        print('This runs at most three times')
+
+    schedule.every(5).seconds.max_runs(3).do(job)
+    schedule.every().max_runs(3).minutes.do(job)
+
+``max_runs`` can be combined with ``until``; the job is removed when either
+limit is reached first.
+
+
 Get all jobs
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 To retrieve all jobs from the scheduler, use ``schedule.get_jobs()``
